100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 13, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, discussing the ongoing tensions in the Far East, particularly regarding Japan's actions in China. In the U.S., the Supreme Court heard arguments in the landmark case of McGrain v. Daugherty, which could set significant precedents for congressional power. Meanwhile, the British government faced criticism over its handling of the Irish Free State, as negotiations for peace continued amidst rising unrest.
